            "15. On Windows, run `install-local.ps1`, `upgrade-local.ps1`, `uninstall-local.ps1`, `archive-local.ps1`, or `local-checks.ps1` from PowerShell; Command Prompt users can run the matching `.cmd` files. These wrappers use `PYTHON_BIN` when set, otherwise they try `python` and then `py -3`.",
            "16. On macOS, double-click `install-local.command`, `upgrade-local.command`, `uninstall-local.command`, `archive-local.command`, or `local-checks.command` when a user prefers a Terminal window over typing commands.",
            f"17. Open `{WRITER_MODE_APPROVAL_MD_FILE}` and parse `{WRITER_MODE_APPROVAL_JSON_FILE}` before switching any local MCP config from read-only to writer mode.",
            "18. Open `client-compatibility.md` or `client-compatibility.json` when you need to know whether this desktop client is locally configured, GUI-verified, and safe for the selected mode.",
