            "23. Open `index.html` when you want a browser view of the same files and local JSON preflight checks for project wizard, source intake, and result evidence.",
            "24. Open `platforms/README.md` or the matching file under `platforms/` for Codex, Cursor, Claude Desktop, or generic JSON MCP setup.",
            "25. Fill `project-wizard.json` when this is a fresh or newly imported project, then run the dry-run command in `project-wizard.md`.",
            "26. Fill `source-intake.json` after the desktop agent parses source material, then inspect it with `source-intake-review.html` and run the dry-run command in `source-intake.md`.",
            "27. Give `agent-start.md` or the matching `agent-start-<platform>.md` file to the desktop agent when starting this novel project.",
            "28. If local MCP is not installed, follow `setup.md`, `install-local.md`, the matching `platforms/` guide, or the planned command in `bootstrap-plan.md`.",
            f"29. Open `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_SESSION_MD_FILE}` or parse `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_SESSION_JSON_FILE}` when you need one place for real desktop-client evidence prompts, check IDs, result files, and local preflight commands.",
