            "31. Open the desktop client and use `checklist.md` to collect real tool-call evidence.",
            "32. Use `real-client-walkthrough.md` when you need a step-by-step desktop-client verification script.",
            "33. Use `client-prompts.md` when you want copy-ready prompts for the desktop agent.",
            "34. Read `result-json-guide.md` before filling the result JSON.",
            "35. Read `evidence-to-results.md` if you copied evidence into `desktop-evidence.txt` and want the CLI to inspect or generate a results JSON draft.",
            "36. Run `desktop_evidence_packet` / `desktop-evidence-packet` from `commands.json` when you want a read-only evidence status report before writing an imported result JSON.",
            f"37. Open `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_REVIEW_HTML_FILE}` to load local results / evidence files in the browser, open `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_REVIEW_MD_FILE}`, or parse `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_REVIEW_JSON_FILE}` for the generated evidence review; run `desktop_evidence_review` / `desktop-evidence-review` when evidence files or saved records changed after pack generation.",
            f"38. Open `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_GAPS_MD_FILE}` or parse `{DESKTOP_EVIDENCE_GAPS_JSON_FILE}` to see missing, failed, weak, or too-generic required evidence; run `desktop_evidence_gaps` / `desktop-evidence-gaps` after editing evidence files.",
            f"39. Fill `{result_file}` with evidence from the desktop client, or review the imported result JSON from `evidence-to-results.md`.",
            "40. Run `desktop_results_doctor` or `imported_desktop_results_doctor` from `commands.json` before recording real desktop-client evidence.",
            f"41. Desktop agents should inspect `{DESKTOP_PACK_COMMANDS_INDEX_JSON_FILE}` before `commands.json` when they need to choose a command group or check write boundaries.",
